cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a deep learning model for disease prediction using multi-modal data, which involves both imaging and non-imaging data. The model incorporates graph convolution and self-attention layers to leverage the individuality of each element of the multi-modal data. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also involves the use of clinical test data, which suggests the possibility of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
